  "prompt": "How early can you check in at the airport for international flight?",
  "response": "The check-in time for international flights can vary depending on the airline, airport, and destination, but here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **Standard Check-In Times**:\n   - **Online Check-In**: Most airlines open online check-in 24 to 48 hours before the flight\u2019s departure.\n   - **Airport Check-In**: Typically opens 3 to 4 hours before departure for international flights.\n\n2. **Early Check-In**:\n   - Some airlines or airports may allow check-in earlier than 3 to 4 hours, but this is less common and usually depends on the airline\u2019s policies and airport facilities.\n\n3. **Cut-Off Times**:\n   - Most airlines require passengers to check in at least 1 hour before departure for international flights, but it\u2019s always best to verify with your specific airline.\n\n4. **Airport Considerations**:\n   - Larger airports with more passengers and security checks may open check-in counters earlier to manage the crowd.\n   - Smaller airports might have more limited hours, so check with the airport or airline in advance.\n\n5. **Special Situations**:\n   - If you have special needs (e.g., traveling with pets, oversized baggage, or requiring special assistance), you may need to arrive earlier.\n   - For flights to countries with stringent security checks (e.g., the U.S.), you may need to comply with additional requirements, such as arriving 3 hours before departure.\n\nAlways check your airline\u2019s specific guidelines and arrive early enough to account for security, customs, and boarding procedures.",
